Sachs: The fallacy of the world: we have no system of croosborder human decency. We promised 1 % to the poor countries; 0,7 public and 0,3 private. We don’t even deliver half. We need to support governments to deliver education, health, infrastructure, environmental protection.

Jeffrey Sachs: “When we talk about financing the SDG’s, we talk about financing government! Universal education and health, water and energy, research etc. are merit goods. The market will not fulfill the needs for the poor” #MoveHumanity #SDGs #Verdensmål https://t.co/ffpW15vAuN
